01:00:11.760 --> 01:00:16.020
So we are not far away.

01:00:16.300 --> 01:00:18.440
Like I think the hard bits are solved

01:00:18.520 --> 01:00:19.640
and that was like resolving

01:00:19.880 --> 01:00:21.880
because it works quite different from Conda.

01:00:22.560 --> 01:00:24.740
You need to like get the individual wheel files

01:00:24.800 --> 01:00:26.020
to get the metadata, et cetera.

01:00:26.220 --> 01:00:27.820
And like that doesn't scale

01:00:27.880 --> 01:00:29.660
if you need all the metadata upfront,

01:00:29.940 --> 01:00:31.220
which is actually the case in Conda.

01:00:31.320 --> 01:00:32.600
You have all the metadata upfront,

01:00:33.140 --> 01:00:34.240
but with PyPI you don't.

01:00:34.360 --> 01:00:35.920
And so we had to make the solver lazy.

01:00:36.260 --> 01:00:39.680
We had to make the solve generic and we are through that process now.

01:00:40.980 --> 01:00:45.060
And now it's basically just engineering work in that sense to integrate it with Pixie.

01:00:45.980 --> 01:00:48.000
